content: Aidan is a name of Irish origin, and it means "fiery one" or "little fire." People with the name Aidan are often described as charismatic, adventurous, and confident individuals who have a natural talent for leadership and creative pursuits. They are also known for their energy, enthusiasm, and determination. Aidan is a strong and unique name with a positive connotation, and it has been a popular choice for parents all over the world.
